<description>Progressing through the ranks, Aaron became a valuable member of the Newcastle United squad due to his defensive versatility.
In an era of big money imports, he was approaching the 300-game mark before departing for Aston Villa.
Aaron's contract at Newcastle United was extended to June 2007 in August 2004 before he joined Aston Villa in May 2005 with a three-year contract.
He joined Fulham in June 2007 in a three-year contract that was extended to June 2013 in December 2009.</description>

